      <conbodydiv class="- topic/bodydiv concept/conbodydiv ">
         <section class="- topic/section ">
            <sectiondiv class="- topic/sectiondiv ">
               <hazardstatement conref="../../Library/Warnings_Library_0000325173.dita#war_lib/high_current_cap-inverter"
                                platform="WxW"
                                class="+ topic/note hazard-d/hazardstatement ">
                  <messagepanel class="+ topic/ul hazard-d/messagepanel ">
                     <typeofhazard class="+ topic/li hazard-d/typeofhazard "/>
                     <howtoavoid class="+ topic/li hazard-d/howtoavoid "/>
                  </messagepanel>
               </hazardstatement>
               <hazardstatement conref="../../Library/Warnings_Library_0000325173.dita#war_lib/high_current_capacitors"
                                platform="PxW SDC"
                                class="+ topic/note hazard-d/hazardstatement ">
                  <messagepanel class="+ topic/ul hazard-d/messagepanel ">
                     <typeofhazard class="+ topic/li hazard-d/typeofhazard "/>
                     <howtoavoid class="+ topic/li hazard-d/howtoavoid "/>
                  </messagepanel>
               </hazardstatement>
               <p class="- topic/p ">A system check is performed
during the commissioning. Pay special attention to specific steps
that are only valid for some configurations and system types.</p>
               <p otherprops="typeS" class="- topic/p ">
                  <b otherprops="generalM" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only for single system: </b>The system check is performed for the system. Afterwards it is in <ph platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/ph ">normal operation</ph>
                  <ph platform="SDC" class="- topic/ph ">float charge</ph>, without any load connected.</p>
               <p otherprops="typeD" class="- topic/p ">
                  <b otherprops="generalM" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only for dual systems: </b>The system check
is performed for one unit at a time, the order of the units does not
matter. Afterwards both units are in normal operation, without any
load connected.</p>
               <p otherprops="typeR" class="- topic/p ">
                  <b otherprops="generalM" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only for redundant systems: </b>The <ph platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/ph ">two first
sections</ph>
                  <ph platform="SDC" class="- topic/ph ">first section</ph> in the system check
is performed for one unit at a time, <u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">starting with unit2</u>. Afterwards <u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">unit2 is in <ph platform="PxW SDC" class="- topic/ph ">standby</ph>
                     <ph platform="WxW" class="- topic/ph ">charger only (standby)</ph>
                  </u> and <u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">unit1 is in <ph platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/ph ">normal operation</ph>
                     <ph platform="SDC" class="- topic/ph ">float charge</ph>
                  </u>, without any load connected.</p>
            </sectiondiv>
         </section>
         <section id="BP_BatteryOperationCheckOnOneUnit-AA6BF085"
                  platform="PxW SDC"
                  class="- topic/section ">
            <title class="- topic/title ">Battery Operation Check on One Unit</title>
            <ol class="- topic/ol ">
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Close the rectifier mains input breaker.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">After about 10 seconds the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> shows <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Standby</codeph>.</p>
                  <note conref="../../Library/Reference_Library_CPT_0000338844.dita#Reference_Library-69E2C789/autostart_start-up"
                        class="- topic/note "/>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Lamp test button</b> and check that all LED’s
on the front panel illuminates. </p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">ON button</b> for one second, if the unit did
not start from the autostart. After a few seconds or if any key is
pressed the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> shows <codeph platform="PxW" class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Normal operation
load power ...%</codeph>
                     <codeph platform="SDC" class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Float charge load ...%</codeph>.</p>
                  <note type="important" class="- topic/note ">
                     <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only for 250 V DC systems: </b>The
output terminal is energized.</note>
               </li>
               <li otherprops="R_CommonBattery" platform="SDC" class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">
                     <b otherprops="generalM" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only for redundant system with a common battery: </b>Close the rectifier output switch.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Number 8 key</b> to check the DC voltage.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p id="battery" class="- topic/p ">If the DC voltage is within tolerance, close the
external battery breaker. The battery is now connected to the unit.</p>
                  <note otherprops="R_CommonBattery" class="- topic/note ">
                     <b otherprops="generalM" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only
for redundant system with a common battery: </b>If the system has
a common battery protection breaker it will already be closed when
performing the check on <u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">unit1</u>.</note>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Number 5 key</b> to check the battery current.</p>
               </li>
               <li platform="PxW" class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Number 9 key</b> to check that
the inverter output voltage is within tolerance. Check that the white
inverter LED on the mimic diagram is illuminated.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Open the rectifier mains input breaker. Check that the unit
changes to battery operation, and that the white battery LED on the
mimic diagram is illuminated. The <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> will show <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Batt. operation time ...min</codeph>.</p>
                  <note class="- topic/note "> The remaining runtime
will only be shown if advanced battery monitor is installed.</note>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Let the unit be in battery operation for 30 seconds to check
that the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Battery operation</b> indication activates on the alarm
panel.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Close the rectifier mains input breaker. Check that the unit
changes to <ph platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/ph ">normal operation</ph>
                     <ph platform="SDC" class="- topic/ph ">float charge</ph>.</p>
               </li>
               <li platform="SDC" class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">
                     <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only for 48 V DC systems: </b>Close the output
breaker.</p>
                  <note type="important" class="- topic/note ">
                     <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only for 48 V DC systems: </b>The output terminal is energized.</note>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Confirm the alarms by pressing the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">C key</b> twice.</p>
               </li>
               <li otherprops="typeR" platform="SDC" class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">
                     <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only for <u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">unit2</u> in
redundant systems with individual batteries: </b>Open the battery
breaker.</p>
               </li>
               <li otherprops="typeR" platform="SDC" class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">
                     <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only for <u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">unit2</u> 
in redundant systems: </b>Press both the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">ON button</b> and the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">OFF button</b> at the same time for two seconds. The <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> now shows <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Standby</codeph>.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Continue with the section:<sl platform="PxW" class="- topic/sl ">
                        <sli class="- topic/sli ">
                           <b otherprops="generalM" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">For all systems with bypass: </b>
                           <xref href="#./BP_BypassOperationCheckOnOneUnit-AA6BEEEC"
                                 scope="local"
                                 type="section"
                                 class="- topic/xref "/>.</sli>
                        <sli class="- topic/sli ">
                           <b otherprops="generalM" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">For single systems without bypass: </b>
                           <xref href="Bruce_Connecting_the_Output_Distribution_CPT_0000916515.dita"
                                 scope="local"
                                 type="concept"
                                 class="- topic/xref "/>.</sli>
                        <sli class="- topic/sli ">
                           <b otherprops="generalM" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">For dual systems without bypass: </b>
                           <xref href="#./BP_AdditionalStepsForDualSystems-8EFBDCC3"
                                 scope="local"
                                 type="section"
                                 class="- topic/xref "/>.</sli>
                        <sli class="- topic/sli ">
                           <b otherprops="generalM" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">For redundant systems without bypass: </b>
                           <xref href="#./BP_AdditionalStepsForRedundantSystems-8EFBDEDE"
                                 scope="local"
                                 type="section"
                                 class="- topic/xref "/>.</sli>
                     </sl>
                     <sl platform="SDC" class="- topic/sl ">
                        <sli otherprops="typeS" class="- topic/sli ">
                           <b otherprops="generalM" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">For single systems: </b>
                           <xref href="Bruce_Connecting_the_Output_Distribution_CPT_0000916515.dita"
                                 scope="local"
                                 type="concept"
                                 class="- topic/xref "/>.</sli>
                        <sli otherprops="typeR" class="- topic/sli ">
                           <b otherprops="generalM" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">For redundant systems: </b>
                           <xref href="#./BP_AdditionalStepsForRedundantSystems-8EFBDEDE"
                                 scope="local"
                                 type="section"
                                 class="- topic/xref "/>.</sli>
                     </sl>
                  </p>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </section>
      </conbodydiv>
      <conbodydiv class="- topic/bodydiv concept/conbodydiv ">
         <section id="BP_StartUpCheckOnOneUnit-20D8C3C2"
                  platform="WxW"
                  class="- topic/section ">
            <title class="- topic/title ">Start Up Check on One Unit</title>
            <note type="important" class="- topic/note "> The DC
capacitors needs to be charged before the inverter input switch is
closed.</note>
            <ol class="- topic/ol ">
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Make sure the external source of the DC input power is available.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Charge the DC capacitors:</p>
                  <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                     <li class="- topic/li ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Keep the charging/discharging switch it in position 2 (charge)
until the warning LED turns off.</p>
                     </li>
                     <li class="- topic/li ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">With the charging/discharging switch still in position 2 (charge),
close the inverter input switch. If not possible, release the charging/discharging
switch and quickly close the inverter input switch.</p>
                     </li>
                     <li class="- topic/li ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Release the charging/discharging switch.</p>
                     </li>
                  </ol>
                  <note conref="../../Library/Reference_Library_CPT_0000338844.dita#Reference_Library-69E2C789/autostart_start-up"
                        class="- topic/note "/>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Lamp test button</b> and check that all LED’s
on the front panel illuminates. </p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">ON button</b> for one second, if the unit did
not start from the autostart. After a few seconds or if any key is
pressed the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> shows <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Normal operation load power
...%</codeph>.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Number 8 key</b> to check the DC voltage.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Number 5 key</b> to check the DC current.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Number 9 key</b> to check that the inverter output
voltage is within tolerance. Check that the white inverter LED on
the mimic diagram is illuminated.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Confirm the alarms by pressing the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">C key</b> twice.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Continue with the section:<sl class="- topic/sl ">
                        <sli otherprops="2pMBS 3pMBS noMBS" class="- topic/sli ">
                           <b otherprops="generalM" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">For all
systems with bypass: </b>
                           <xref href="#./BP_BypassOperationCheckOnOneUnit-AA6BEEEC"
                                 scope="local"
                                 type="section"
                                 class="- topic/xref "/>.</sli>
                        <sli otherprops="noByp" class="- topic/sli ">
                           <b otherprops="generalM" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">For single systems
without bypass: </b>
                           <xref href="Bruce_Connecting_the_Output_Distribution_CPT_0000916515.dita"
                                 scope="local"
                                 type="concept"
                                 class="- topic/xref "/>.</sli>
                        <sli otherprops="typeD noByp" class="- topic/sli ">
                           <b otherprops="generalM" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">For dual systems
without bypass: </b>
                           <xref href="#./BP_AdditionalStepsForDualSystems-8EFBDCC3"
                                 scope="local"
                                 type="section"
                                 class="- topic/xref "/>.</sli>
                        <sli otherprops="typeR noByp" class="- topic/sli ">
                           <b otherprops="generalM" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">For redundant
systems without bypass: </b>
                           <xref href="#./BP_AdditionalStepsForRedundantSystems-8EFBDEDE"
                                 scope="local"
                                 type="section"
                                 class="- topic/xref "/>.</sli>
                     </sl>
                  </p>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </section>
