      <section id="BP_BypassOperationCheckOnOneUnit-AA6BEEEC"
               otherprops="2pMBS 3pMBS noMBS"
               platform="PxW WxW"
               class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">Bypass Operation
Check on One Unit</title>
         <hazardstatement conref="../../Library/Warnings_Library_0000325173.dita#war_lib/output_energized"
                          class="+ topic/note hazard-d/hazardstatement ">
            <messagepanel class="+ topic/ul hazard-d/messagepanel ">
               <typeofhazard class="+ topic/li hazard-d/typeofhazard "/>
               <howtoavoid class="+ topic/li hazard-d/howtoavoid "/>
            </messagepanel>
         </hazardstatement>
         <note otherprops="2pMBS 3pMBS noMBS" class="- topic/note ">
            <b otherprops="generalM" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">For systems with a manual bypass switch: </b>Check the position of the manual bypass switch. It should be in <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Bypass</b> except if the check is performed on <u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">unit1</u> in a
redundant system with a common manual bypass switch.</note>
         <ol class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Close the bypass mains input breaker. </p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p "> If applicable, close the bypass isolation switch.</p>
            </li>
            <li otherprops="generalM 3pMBS" class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">
                  <b otherprops="tempExclude" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only
for 3-position manual bypass switch: </b>Turn the manual bypass switch
to the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Test</b> position. <note class="- topic/note ">
                     <b otherprops="generalM" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only for
redundant systems with common manual bypass: </b>The manual bypass
switch will already be in the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Test</b> position when performing
the check for <u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">unit1</u>.</note>
               </p>
            </li>
            <li otherprops="2pMBS" class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Close the bypass isolation (EN input) switch.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Check that the blue inverter LED on the mimic diagram is illuminated,
indicating that the inverter is synchronized with the bypass mains.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Check that the white LED before the static switch EN (upstream)
on the mimic diagram is illuminated, indicating that the bypass mains
is available and within tolerance.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Switch to bypass operation:<ol conref="Bruce_How_to_Switch_from_Normal_Operation_to_Bypass_Operation_CPT_0000916381.dita#HowToSwitchFromNormalOperationToByp-74A61565/BP_Switch-to-bypass"
                      class="- topic/ol ">
                     <li class="- topic/li "/>
                  </ol>
               </p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Check that the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> shows <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Bypass operation</codeph>.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Switch back to normal operation:</p>
               <ol conref="Bruce_How_to_Switch_from_Bypass_Operation_to_Normal_Operation_CPT_0000916380.dita#HowToSwitchFromBypassOperationToNor-74A64CEF/BP_Switch-to-normal"
                   class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li "/>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Check that the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> shows <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Normal operation
load power ...%</codeph>.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Confirm any alarms by pressing the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">C key</b> twice.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">
                  <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only for <u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">unit2</u> in redundant systems: </b>Press both
the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">ON button</b> and the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">OFF button</b> at the same time for
two seconds. The <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> now shows <codeph platform="PxW" class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Standby</codeph>
                  <codeph platform="WxW" class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Charger only</codeph>
                  <ph platform="WxW" class="- topic/ph "> (standby)</ph>.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Continue with the section:<sl class="- topic/sl ">
                     <sli otherprops="typeS" class="- topic/sli ">
                        <b otherprops="generalM" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">For single or dual
units with manual bypass switch(es): </b>
                        <xref href="#./BP_SetManualBypassSwitchesToAuto-AA6C103D"
                              scope="local"
                              type="section"
                              class="- topic/xref "/>.</sli>
                     <sli otherprops="noByp" class="- topic/sli ">
                        <b otherprops="generalM" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">For single units
without manual bypass switch(es): </b>
                        <xref href="Bruce_Connecting_the_Output_Distribution_CPT_0000916515.dita"
                              scope="local"
                              type="concept"
                              class="- topic/xref "/>.</sli>
                     <sli otherprops="typeD" class="- topic/sli ">
                        <b otherprops="generalM" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">For dual units without
manual bypass switch(es): </b>
                        <xref href="#./BP_AdditionalStepsForDualSystems-8EFBDCC3"
                              scope="local"
                              type="section"
                              class="- topic/xref "/>.</sli>
                     <sli otherprops="typeR" class="- topic/sli ">
                        <b otherprops="generalM" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">For redundant systems: </b>
                        <xref href="#./BP_AdditionalStepsForRedundantSystems-8EFBDEDE"
                              scope="local"
                              type="section"
                              class="- topic/xref "/>.</sli>
                  </sl>
               </p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </section>
      <section id="BP_AdditionalStepsForRedundantSystems-8EFBDEDE"
               otherprops="typeR"
               class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">Additional Steps for Redundant Systems</title>
         <sectiondiv class="- topic/sectiondiv ">
            <ol class="- topic/ol ">
               <li platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Repeat the relevant sections for <u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">unit1</u>:<ol class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li platform="PxW" class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p ">
                              <xref href="#./BP_BatteryOperationCheckOnOneUnit-AA6BF085"
                                    scope="local"
                                    type="section"
                                    class="- topic/xref "/>.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li platform="WxW" class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p ">
                              <xref href="#./BP_StartUpCheckOnOneUnit-20D8C3C2"
                                    scope="local"
                                    type="section"
                                    class="- topic/xref "/>
                           </p>
                        </li>
                        <li otherprops="2pMBS 3pMBS noMBS"
                            platform="PxW WxW"
                            class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p ">
                              <xref href="#./BP_BypassOperationCheckOnOneUnit-AA6BEEEC"
                                    scope="local"
                                    type="section"
                                    class="- topic/xref "/>.</p>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li platform="SDC" class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Repeat the <xref href="#./BP_BatteryOperationCheckOnOneUnit-AA6BF085"
                           scope="local"
                           type="section"
                           class="- topic/xref "/> section for <u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">unit1</u>.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Check that the <ph platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/ph ">redundant communication
cables are</ph>
                     <ph platform="SDC" class="- topic/ph ">parallel communication cable is</ph> connected according to the specifications in the <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Connection Diagram</i>.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">
                     <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only for <u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">unit2</u>: </b>Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">ON button</b> for
one second to restart <u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">unit2</u>.<ph platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/ph "> Check that
the blue inverter LED on the mimic diagrams is illuminated.</ph>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Check that the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Displays</b> on both units show <codeph platform="PxW WxW" class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Normal operation load power ...%</codeph>
                     <codeph platform="SDC" class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Float charge load ...%</codeph>.</p>
               </li>
               <li platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Close <u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">both</u> output isolation switches.</p>
               </li>
               <li otherprops="R_CommonBattery" platform="SDC" class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">
                     <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only for <u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">unit2</u> in redundant systems with individual batteries: </b>Close
the battery breaker.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Confirm any alarms by pressing the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">C key</b> twice.</p>
               </li>
               <li platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Check that alarms for the parallel communication
are not active.</p>
               </li>
               <li platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Continue with the section <xref href="#./BP_SetManualBypassSwitchesToAuto-AA6C103D"
                           scope="local"
                           type="section"
                           class="- topic/xref "/>.</p>
               </li>
               <li platform="SDC" class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">After both units are checked and in float charge,
continue with the section <xref href="Bruce_Connecting_the_Output_Distribution_CPT_0000916515.dita"
                           scope="local"
                           type="concept"
                           class="- topic/xref "/>.</p>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </sectiondiv>
      </section>
      <section id="BP_SetManualBypassSwitchesToAuto-AA6C103D"
               otherprops="2pMBS 3pMBS noMBS"
               platform="PxW WxW"
               class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">Set Manual
Bypass Switch to Normal and Check Parallel Communication</title>
         <p otherprops="typeR" class="- topic/p ">
            <b otherprops="generalM" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only for redundant systems: </b>This procedure is performed to verify that the parallel communication
is working as intended. Only switch operation from <u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">unit1</u> and
check that <u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">unit2</u> reacts in the same way.</p>
         <ol class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Switch the unit to bypass operation:</p>
               <ol conref="Bruce_How_to_Switch_from_Normal_Operation_to_Bypass_Operation_CPT_0000916381.dita#HowToSwitchFromNormalOperationToByp-74A61565/BP_Switch-to-bypass"
                   class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li "/>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p "> Check that the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> shows <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Bypass operation</codeph>.</p>
            </li>
            <li otherprops="typeR" class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">
                  <b otherprops="generalM" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only for redundant
system: </b>Check that <u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">unit2</u> also switched to bypass operation.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Check that the white LED after the inverter (downstream) on
the mimic diagram is illuminated, indicating that the inverter output
is available and within tolerance.</p>
            </li>
            <li otherprops="2pMBS 3pMBS" class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">
                  <b otherprops="generalM" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only for
systems with manual bypass switch(es): </b>If the inverter output
is available and within tolerance, switch the manual bypass switch
to the position <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Normal</b>.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Switch the unit to normal operation:</p>
               <ol conref="Bruce_How_to_Switch_from_Bypass_Operation_to_Normal_Operation_CPT_0000916380.dita#HowToSwitchFromBypassOperationToNor-74A64CEF/BP_Switch-to-normal"
                   class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li "/>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p "> Check that the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> shows <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Normal operation
load power ...%</codeph>.</p>
            </li>
            <li otherprops="typeR" class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">
                  <b otherprops="generalM" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only for redundant
system: </b>Check that <u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">unit2</u> also switched to normal operation.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Confirm any alarms by pressing the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">C key</b> twice.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Continue with the section:<sl class="- topic/sl ">
                     <sli otherprops="typeS typeR" class="- topic/sli ">
                        <b otherprops="generalM" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">For single
and redundant systems: </b>
                        <xref href="Bruce_Connecting_the_Output_Distribution_CPT_0000916515.dita"
                              scope="local"
                              type="concept"
                              class="- topic/xref "/>.</sli>
                     <sli otherprops="typeD" class="- topic/sli ">
                        <b otherprops="generalM" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">For dual systems: </b>
                        <xref href="#./BP_AdditionalStepsForDualSystems-8EFBDCC3"
                              scope="local"
                              type="section"
                              class="- topic/xref "/>.</sli>
                  </sl>
               </p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </section>
